pages.text: Once upon a time, there was a young boy named Jake. He lived near a big, magical woods that he loved to explore. Every day, Jake would put on his adventure hat and venture into the woods to discover new things.

One sunny morning, as Jake was walking through the woods, he heard a noise. It sounded like it was coming from behind a tall tree. Jake's curious eyes sparkled with excitement. What could it be? He tiptoed closer and peeked around the tree.

To his surprise, Jake discovered a friendly squirrel nibbling on acorns. The squirrel looked up and chattered happily, as if it was saying hello to Jake. Jake couldn't help but giggle. The squirrel hopped onto Jake's shoulder and together they continued exploring the woods.

They climbed trees, splashed in little puddles, and even found a cozy hidden spot to have a picnic. Jake and his new squirrel friend had so much fun! When it started to get dark, Jake knew it was time to head back home. He gently said goodbye to the squirrel and thanked him for the wonderful adventure.

As Jake walked back to his house, he couldn't stop smiling. He couldn't wait to tell his family about the amazing day he had in the woods. From that day on, Jake and the squirrel became the best of friends and would often go on little woodland adventures together.
And so, the woods and all its mystical creatures became Jake's favorite place in the whole wide world. He knew that every day held a new adventure, just waiting for him to discover it. The end.
